hopobject.body: I support Manchester United foodpharm.net It's easy to complain about the state of American STEM education, but it goes without saying that fixing the education system's deficiencies in this area is a complex problem. One reason is that there are plenty of misconceptions and generalizations out there about the state of STEM. On a Tuesday panel at the 2013 U.S. News STEM Solutions conference, educators and STEM advocates shot holes in what they consider to be myths about STEM.
